The paper deals with the problem of cooperative intersection management, which is a common problem in automated transportation systems for people or goods, as well as in multi-robot environments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for optimal algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MA) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper proposes a mathematical framework for solving the problem, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a locally optimal algorithm, which suggests that it may also belong to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
